Directions: From trail junction 1 mile southwest of Laurel Lake, go uphill toward Laurel Lake for 4 1/2 cains to a CADE 5 m off trail on left (north) side (~2m DBH).  From tree, go 1.5 chains at 353 degrees into a group of QUKE resprouts to A stake.

Directions: Hike the west side of Laurel Lake toward the north side of the lake.  Look for the first established campsite on the lake side of the trail as the trail bends to the east around the northern edge of Laurel Lake.  On the trail near camp is a large PIJE (~1.5 m DBH) with a distinct lean.  From tree, go 7 chains at 18 degrees to rock about 1 m high and 4 m long (that looks like a partly-buried, giant rhino's back).  From rhino, go 2.5 chains at 312 degrees to A stake, stopping ~15 m short of a shack-sized boulder.
MetaData: Subsample comments:  5mA:  5mB:  fuels:  herbA:  herbB:  overstory:  saplings:  seedlings:

Directions: Hike down trail from Laurel Lake (toward Lake Eleanor).  At the junction with the trail toward Beehive Meadow, walk around 16 chains east (toward Beehive Meadow) to a boulder on the north side of trail (2 m tall).  From the boulder, go 3 chains at 33 degrees to the A stake.  --OR--  Take the Beehive Trail down (south) and go west at the junction toward Lake Eleanor.  Hike on that trail for a while... cross Frog creek and eventually a small minor drainage.  From the minor drainage, hike another 5 chains along the trail until the boulder (see above).

Directions: From Laurel Lake, hike down the trail toward Lake Eleanor.  At junction with the Beehive trail, head east toward Beehive (and Hetchy).  From the junction, walk along trail (east) about 23 chains to a small drainage (you will also pass the boulder reference feature for plot 5).  From the small drainage, hike another 10.5 chains east to a 1 m+ DBH PILA on the north side of trail.  From PILA, walk 4.5 chains at 359 degrees to the A stake.
